    "created_at": "2015-06-03T09:42:16Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-06-03T09:42:16Z",
    "body": "I followed your suggestion, at the end using the [request module](https://github.com/request/request) which makes writing the http post request a little nicer\n\nIt worked at the first try, thanks a lot @zcbenz, you've made us very happy :)\n\n```\nnodeRequest = require('request')\n\nformData =\n  file:\n    value: fs.createReadStream( fileLocation )\n    options:\n      filename: filename\n\nnodeRequest.post {\n  url: url\n  formData: formData\n}, (err, httpResponse, body) ->\n  if err\n    console.error('upload failed:', err)\n  console.log 'Upload successful!  Server responded with:', body\n```\n"
